<section class="space-y-4">
  <p>
    Agent, welcome to <span class="text-cyan-300 font-semibold">AgentArchive</span>, the central archive of the operations unit.
    After NULL's attack, the system no longer knows which agents exist, which skills they possess, or which missions they are assigned to.
  </p>

  <div class="rounded-xl border border-cyan-900/70 bg-cyan-950/20 p-4">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-500 mb-3">Domain model</div>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-gray-200 marker:text-cyan-400">
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Agents</span> — operational actors in the system</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Skills</span> — capabilities owned by agents</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Missions</span> — assignments linked to agents</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gray-500 mb-3">Recovery steps</div>
    <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5 marker:text-cyan-400">
      <li>
        Create the <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">Agent</code> model and a migration with
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">codename:string</code>,
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">level:integer</code>, and
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">active:boolean</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Add the <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">Skill</code> model with
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">name:string</code> and
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">category:string</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Add <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">Mission</code> and
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">AgentSkill</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Configure associations:
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 marker:text-cyan-400 text-gray-300">
          <li>an agent has many missions;</li>
          <li>an agent has many skills through a join table;</li>
          <li>a skill can belong to many agents.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Add validations for required fields, uniqueness and mission statuses.
        Agent codenames must be unique, level must be a number between 1 and 10,
        and mission status may be one of "assigned", "in_progress", or "completed".
      </li>
      <li>
        Protect the schema with database constraints: foreign keys, unique indexes, and a composite index on
        <code class="rounded bg-gray-950 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-green-300">[agent_id, skill_id]</code>.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

</section>
